LEX Escrow.

"Buyer" is a person.
"Seller" is a person.
"Agent" is a person.
"Amount" is an amount.

The Buyer pays an Amount into escrow, appoints the Seller, appoints the Agent.

CLAUSE: Pay Out.
The Agent may pay the escrow to the Seller.

CLAUSE: Pay Back.
The Agent may pay the escrow to the Buyer.

